Explanation of how the parameters were derived:

- The controller method handling POST /printshops/{printShopID}/employees is ManagerController.addEmployee(long psid, HttpServletRequest request).
- The method uses @PathVariable(value = "printShopID") long psid, so the operation requires a path parameter named "printShopID" of type long (integer with int64 format) and that parameter is required.
- The method reads the request body via request.getInputStream() and deserializes it with GSON.fromJson(requestJSON, Employee.class). The code then checks that the deserialized Employee has non-null getName(), getUsername(), and getPassword() before proceeding. Thus the body must be JSON representing an Employee and must include the fields username, password and name.
- To avoid using $ref, the body parameter schema is expanded inline as an object with properties username, password and name (all strings) and with a required list containing those three fields.

